                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Poor</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; red.</seg>
                        <date>First half of the 20th century.</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; 
 the word mǝʿrāf;
 a few
                           lines (in both columns) in the incipit page of each text, divided into
                           two, three or four groups, alternating with black lines (2 lines in fol.
                           6r, 9 lines on fol. 44r, 5 lines on fol. 64r, 8 lines on fol. 101r); the
                           Canon tables; 
 the incipits of the parts of the Introduction (fols.
                           6ra – 13va) and of the chapters of the Gospels;
 the title of each
                           Gospel; the chapters titles;
 Ethiopic numerals of the “tituli”;
                           the horizontal dashes above and below Ethiopic numerals; 
 elements
                           of the punctuation signs;
 name of Walatta Madḫǝn, one of the
                           donors(fol. 43vb, l.22); names of the church feasts in the upper margin
                           of some fols. indicating the Gospel readings.</seg>
                     </handNote>
